The paper deals with distributed computing on large-scale graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) since the paper explicitly mentions a message-passing model for distributed computing. The paper also deals with fundamental graph problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper mentions graph partitioning, which is a common problem in cs.NE (Networks and Networking). Finally, the paper deals with graph connectivity and verification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
